genresAdvancedInfo.name: charango
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Charango - Charango is a traditional Andean instrument that resembles a small guitar. The music genre focuses on the use of the charango as the main instrument, accompanied by other traditional instruments such as the quena and zampona. The music is characterized by its upbeat and lively rhythms, often played at celebrations and festivals.
